WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:44.880 --> 00:00:47.540
Get moving right now, get moving right now

3
00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:50.630
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

4
00:00:56.940 --> 00:00:59.670
Setting out all on our own to cross the endless sea,

5
00:00:59.670 --> 00:01:02.230
you know what we're searching for

6
00:01:03.030 --> 00:01:05.980
The worldwide enigma, treasures undiscovered

7
00:01:06.070 --> 00:01:08.110
Picking's ripe, so let's go explore

8
00:01:08.990 --> 00:01:12.130
We're all so excited, our hearts can't keep quiet

9
00:01:12.130 --> 00:01:13.880
Nothing left to do but press on

10
00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:19.760
Trailing after footprints left by the dreamers before us

11
00:01:20.590 --> 00:01:23.560
Stormy nights can try their best to sink us

12
00:01:23.560 --> 00:01:26.560
We'll sail on, if we just stick together

13
00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:30.710
Try and stop us if you can

14
00:01:30.850 --> 00:01:32.030
We always pull through

15
00:01:32.930 --> 00:01:35.760
Get moving right now, get moving right now

16
00:01:35.890 --> 00:01:38.720
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

17
00:01:38.770 --> 00:01:41.310
Even if we sometimes shed tears,

18
00:01:41.400 --> 00:01:44.750
and want to hide them from prying eyes

19
00:01:44.940 --> 00:01:47.690
But go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

20
00:01:47.860 --> 00:01:50.690
Run the direction the compass points in

21
00:01:50.670 --> 00:01:52.550
Stop it! Saul!

22
00:01:50.780 --> 00:01:53.400
All our dreams are straight ahead it says

23
00:01:52.550 --> 00:01:53.890
Get ready!

24
00:01:53.400 --> 00:01:55.570
So don't sit back, let's chase it

25
00:01:53.890 --> 00:01:58.470
Making an enemy of me
will be the last thing you do!

26
00:01:56.890 --> 00:02:00.850
<b>Declaration of War</b>

27
00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:05.660
Get moving right now, get moving right now

28
00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:08.710
We have to pull through ahead of them all

29
00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:11.290
If we hold firm and stand our ground,

30
00:02:10.360 --> 00:02:11.690
What's going on?!

31
00:02:11.390 --> 00:02:14.710
I know the future's within our grasp

32
00:02:11.690 --> 00:02:13.530
It's Vice Admiral Saul!

33
00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:18.990
First he escapes with Olvia,
and now he's attacking us!

34
00:02:14.770 --> 00:02:17.800
So go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

35
00:02:17.850 --> 00:02:20.680
The world's our oyster, it's waiting for us

36
00:02:19.490 --> 00:02:21.000
Why is he here?!

37
00:02:20.730 --> 00:02:23.100
All the sadness and the joy we see,

38
00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:23.000
W-We don't know!

39
00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:25.600
let's etch it in our hearts

40
00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:27.670
The island's done for!

41
00:02:27.670 --> 00:02:29.500
It'll all burn to ash!

42
00:02:29.500 --> 00:02:32.130
Don't give up! Save the books!

43
00:02:32.130 --> 00:02:33.840
History must be told!

44
00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:37.140
Throw them into the lake!

45
00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:39.720
It's better than letting them burn up! Hurry!

46
00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:44.520
Now!

47
00:02:48.110 --> 00:02:51.070
Saul! Stop it already! You'll die!

48
00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:54.070
Throw the books out of the library!

49
00:02:54.070 --> 00:02:55.950
Save as many as possible!

50
00:02:55.950 --> 00:02:58.830
Preserve as many pages as you can!

51
00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:03.000
So that thousands of years
of our ancestors' words...

52
00:03:02.450 --> 00:03:05.370
...will reach the future!

53
00:03:08.920 --> 00:03:11.210
Robin! What are you doing?!

54
00:03:11.210 --> 00:03:13.510
Run to the evacuation ship while you can!

55
00:03:13.510 --> 00:03:16.800
You won't survive if you stay on this island!

56
00:03:51.170 --> 00:03:53.300
Mom!

57
00:03:58.380 --> 00:04:00.260
Fire at Saul!

58
00:04:01.350 --> 00:04:03.720
Robin! Hurry up and run!

59
00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:06.810
Remember your mother's last wish!

60
00:04:06.850 --> 00:04:10.610
Live, Robin!

61
00:04:10.610 --> 00:04:13.020
The evacuation ship is departing!

62
00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:15.280
Wait! There's someone coming!

63
00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:16.690
That's...!

64
00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:19.950
Isn't that the monster?!

65
00:04:19.950 --> 00:04:21.120
Yeah, it is!

66
00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:22.700
Go away, monster!

67
00:04:22.700 --> 00:04:24.700
Hey! Don't be ridiculous!

68
00:04:24.700 --> 00:04:26.120
Well... wait!

69
00:04:26.120 --> 00:04:30.670
Isn't she the daughter of Olvia,
that criminal who was in the paper?

70
00:04:31.170 --> 00:04:35.210
That's right! If we let her on the ship,
it might cause us trouble too!

71
00:04:35.210 --> 00:04:38.420
That's ridiculous! She's just a kid!
Hurry and bring her aboard!

72
00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:41.680
Evacuation ship, do not let that brat on board!

73
00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:42.720
What?

74
00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:45.430
She may be a child,
but she's also an archaeologist!

75
00:04:45.430 --> 00:04:47.680
She's one of this operation's targets!

76
00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:51.150
Chief Spandine! I-Is that true?!

77
00:04:51.150 --> 00:04:54.020
See? If we had let her
on board, we'd be in danger!

78
00:04:54.400 --> 00:04:55.480
Robin!

79
00:04:56.110 --> 00:04:58.690
CP9?! Of all the useless...!

80
00:04:59.150 --> 00:05:02.200
Chief! Vice Admiral Saul is coming this way!

81
00:05:02.200 --> 00:05:06.160
Really?! I guess we didn't
have to ask Olvia about his whereabouts.

82
00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:08.000
Fire! Fire! Fire the cannons at him!

83
00:05:11.120 --> 00:05:12.380
Ice Block!

84
00:05:12.630 --> 00:05:13.920
Partisan!

85
00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:18.670
Saul!

86
00:05:27.180 --> 00:05:28.520
It's Kuzan!

87
00:05:29.350 --> 00:05:30.640
Kuzan!

88
00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:32.140
Well, well, well...

89
00:05:32.140 --> 00:05:38.070
It'd be a bad look if a deserter
obstructed a buster call, y'know?

90
00:05:38.070 --> 00:05:40.030
Kuzan!

91
00:05:40.030 --> 00:05:43.780
Are you proud of what's happening here?

92
00:05:43.780 --> 00:05:45.280
Pull back!

93
00:05:45.620 --> 00:05:48.620
This ain't right! You damn well know that!

94
00:05:48.620 --> 00:05:50.040
To set an example...!

95
00:05:50.040 --> 00:05:53.420
Ohara is being annihilated to set an example!

96
00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:57.170
If it benefits the future
of the world, then so be it!

97
00:05:57.170 --> 00:06:00.300
In fact, these scholars
have broken the law, right?

98
00:06:00.300 --> 00:06:04.300
Depending on your point of view,
justice can take on a whole new meaning.

99
00:06:04.300 --> 00:06:06.850
So I won't criticize your version of it.

100
00:06:07.390 --> 00:06:10.980
However, if you're thinking
of getting in our way...

101
00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:12.440
I can't ignore it.

102
00:06:21.690 --> 00:06:23.570
The evacuation ship was destroyed!

103
00:06:23.570 --> 00:06:25.660
Wh-Why...?

104
00:06:25.660 --> 00:06:27.660
A battleship... fired on it!

105
00:06:27.660 --> 00:06:30.080
It came from Vice Admiral Sakazuki's ship!

106
00:06:31.250 --> 00:06:32.910
That idiot...!

107
00:06:32.910 --> 00:06:35.580
We must be thorough in our endeavors.

108
00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:36.380
<b>Vice Admiral Sakazuki
Marine Headquarters
(Later to Become
Admiral Akainu)</b>

109
00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:39.170
If even a single scholar
was hiding on that ship...

110
00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:42.170
our sacrifices here would have been in vain.

111
00:06:42.920 --> 00:06:46.470
We must eradicate even
the smallest possibility of evil.

112
00:06:46.470 --> 00:06:48.510
You call this justice?!

113
00:06:48.510 --> 00:06:51.180
Can you still claim the moral high ground?!

114
00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:53.940
Don't lump me in with that moron!

115
00:06:54.600 --> 00:06:56.400
We're making a run for it, Robin!

116
00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:58.860
His strength is out of this world!

117
00:06:58.860 --> 00:07:00.480
Saul ran away!

118
00:07:00.480 --> 00:07:02.530
He's taking a scholar with him!

119
00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:07.070
Ice Time Capsule!

120
00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:13.410
Saul! Are you okay?!

121
00:07:15.750 --> 00:07:18.000
Robin, run away!

122
00:07:22.960 --> 00:07:25.090
Run with all your might!

123
00:07:25.090 --> 00:07:27.470
You'll die if you stay on the island!

124
00:07:27.470 --> 00:07:29.470
Sail out to sea on my raft!

125
00:07:29.470 --> 00:07:30.760
What about you, Saul?

126
00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:34.770
I'm done for. He got me good.

127
00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:36.600
Go!

128
00:07:36.600 --> 00:07:39.190
No! I don't want to be alone at sea!

129
00:07:39.190 --> 00:07:41.520
Listen carefully, Robin!

130
00:07:42.270 --> 00:07:44.280
Although you're alone now,

131
00:07:44.280 --> 00:07:47.530
you're sure to meet some friends someday!

132
00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:52.160
Friends?

133
00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:53.410
That's right.

134
00:07:53.410 --> 00:07:56.910
The sea is vast, so someday...

135
00:07:57.960 --> 00:08:01.170
you'll find friends who'll protect you!

136
00:08:01.170 --> 00:08:05.760
No one is ever born
into this world completely alone!

137
00:08:08.970 --> 00:08:12.430
Run, Robin! Don't look back!

138
00:08:12.430 --> 00:08:16.730
When the pain gets to be too much,
laugh like this, just like I taught you!

139
00:08:16.730 --> 00:08:18.390
Watch out, Saul!

140
00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:23.070
Ice Time.

141
00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:26.650
Saul!

142
00:08:28.070 --> 00:08:31.530
Somewhere in the vast sea
you'll find true friends.

143
00:08:31.530 --> 00:08:34.040
They're out there waiting for you, Robin!

144
00:08:37.910 --> 00:08:42.130
True friends you can live a real life with...!

145
00:08:55.220 --> 00:08:56.270
It's hopeless!

146
00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:59.890
So, this is the history humanity has chosen.

147
00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:03.270
How thoughtless we can be...

148
00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:06.780
I'm sorry, Robin.

149
00:09:09.110 --> 00:09:11.610
I couldn't even give you...

150
00:09:13.870 --> 00:09:15.910
any parting words as your mother.

151
00:09:16.410 --> 00:09:19.830
The Tree of Knowledge... has fallen!

152
00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:32.050
The idea of absolute justice
has been known to drive people mad.

153
00:09:32.470 --> 00:09:35.430
I've decided to let you
escape from this island.

154
00:09:35.430 --> 00:09:39.480
I wonder what could sprout
from the seed Saul tended to?

155
00:09:39.480 --> 00:09:42.690
Whom you bear a grudge against is up to you,

156
00:09:42.690 --> 00:09:46.440
but for now, just be happy you're alive.

157
00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:48.690
Try to keep a low profile.

158
00:09:49.440 --> 00:09:51.950
I've laid a track of ice on the sea.

159
00:09:52.320 --> 00:09:56.410
If you just go straight
in that small boat, you'll reach land.

160
00:09:56.410 --> 00:09:58.910
Now, remember this:

161
00:10:00.870 --> 00:10:02.500
I'm not your ally.

162
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:07.210
I'm your enemy. I'll be the first
to come after you if you cause trouble.

163
00:10:08.340 --> 00:10:10.260
My mom is on the island!

164
00:10:10.590 --> 00:10:12.590
No one will survive.

165
00:10:12.590 --> 00:10:15.800
If the pain is too much to bear...
the choice is yours.

166
00:10:17.390 --> 00:10:19.890
This is the greatest library in the world.

167
00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:22.390
Do you like books?

168
00:10:22.430 --> 00:10:25.150
Today is Robin's birthday!

169
00:10:25.190 --> 00:10:28.270
– Happy birthday, Robin!
– Happy birthday, Robin!

170
00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:29.940
Hold your head high, Robin!

171
00:10:29.940 --> 00:10:31.860
Ohara is honorable!

172
00:10:31.900 --> 00:10:37.410
We cannot forsake
the future of your generation!

173
00:10:37.450 --> 00:10:39.450
So laugh.

174
00:10:39.450 --> 00:10:41.790
When the pain gets
to be too much, just laugh.

175
00:10:42.370 --> 00:10:44.710
It seems dumb to laugh
when you're in pain.

176
00:10:44.750 --> 00:10:46.880
That's not true.

177
00:11:22.290 --> 00:11:28.290
Somewhere in the vast sea you'll find true friends.
They're out there waiting for you, Robin!

178
00:11:45.600 --> 00:11:47.390
Survivors?

179
00:11:47.390 --> 00:11:48.690
Not a chance.

180
00:11:49.270 --> 00:11:49.940
Hey!

181
00:11:49.940 --> 00:11:51.020
Huh?

182
00:11:51.020 --> 00:11:52.610
Take a look at this lake.

183
00:11:53.860 --> 00:11:55.610
Th-The lake...

184
00:12:01.580 --> 00:12:04.290
There are enough books
to completely fill the lake!

185
00:12:04.290 --> 00:12:06.000
Was this by chance?!

186
00:12:06.580 --> 00:12:08.290
Yeah, this is the brat!

187
00:12:08.290 --> 00:12:10.540
There's no doubt about it!

188
00:12:10.540 --> 00:12:12.420
Where was she?! Did you catch her?!

189
00:12:12.420 --> 00:12:15.420
No, sir! We followed a lead
about a suspicious girl

190
00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:20.550
and managed to find her on a passenger ship
leaving an island far northeast of Ohara,

191
00:12:20.550 --> 00:12:22.300
but we soon lost sight of her.

192
00:12:23.510 --> 00:12:25.470
She's got the devil's luck.

193
00:12:25.470 --> 00:12:33.400
Back then, when Ohara was engulfed in flames,
I did see a brat escaping on a small boat!

194
00:12:34.070 --> 00:12:39.240
But before I could chase after her,
the helm got stuck like it was frozen in place.

195
00:12:39.240 --> 00:12:42.490
I bet Saul let her escape right before he died!

196
00:12:43.120 --> 00:12:45.410
If she can decipher the poneglyphs,

197
00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:48.830
she's dangerous regardless of her youth.

198
00:12:49.460 --> 00:12:55.800
Use all available means toward her immediate capture,
or else this operation will amount to nothing!

199
00:13:00.260 --> 00:13:02.140
Seventy-nine million berries?!

200
00:13:02.140 --> 00:13:05.010
A bounty that high for an eight-year-old girl?!

201
00:13:05.010 --> 00:13:10.230
They say she's a survivor of those Ohara devils
who were plotting the world's destruction.

202
00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:12.150
Ohara?

203
00:13:12.150 --> 00:13:17.030
I don't know how, but they say
that she sank six Marine battleships.

204
00:13:17.030 --> 00:13:18.780
That explains the high bounty.

205
00:13:19.280 --> 00:13:22.700
I heard the government and
Marine HQ themselves are hunting her.

206
00:13:23.160 --> 00:13:27.200
Seems like she inherited the ideology
of the executed scholars.

207
00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:28.660
She can't be left at large.

208
00:13:29.160 --> 00:13:33.130
She's a devil's spawn
who shouldn't be left alive!

209
00:13:34.500 --> 00:13:37.050
Thank you for always helping me.

210
00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.050
Oh, no.

211
00:13:38.050 --> 00:13:40.220
Thank you for letting me work.

212
00:13:40.220 --> 00:13:44.930
By the way, before we eat lunch,
there are some guests here to see you.

213
00:13:44.930 --> 00:13:46.140
What?!

214
00:13:46.140 --> 00:13:47.470
Don't let her get away!

215
00:13:47.470 --> 00:13:51.440
Now, pay up! I'm the one who
gave you the tip, after all!

216
00:13:52.100 --> 00:13:54.940
She's small, but she works very hard.

217
00:13:57.020 --> 00:13:59.530
Oh? You're still awake?

218
00:13:59.530 --> 00:14:01.530
We have to go shopping in the morning.

219
00:14:01.530 --> 00:14:02.780
Get some rest soon.

220
00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:03.610
Okay.

221
00:14:04.110 --> 00:14:07.620
She's a good kid, but letting her
stay here puts us at risk too.

222
00:14:08.160 --> 00:14:10.540
And besides, look at this bounty!

223
00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:14.040
Honey! She isn't in her room!

224
00:14:14.040 --> 00:14:17.250
Dammit! The little brat caught on!

225
00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:26.260
I'm sorry. I don't have any food.

226
00:14:32.270 --> 00:14:35.400
I know about you, Nico Robin!

227
00:14:35.900 --> 00:14:38.070
I'm a wanted man myself.

228
00:14:38.610 --> 00:14:41.240
If you help out around here, you get fed.

229
00:14:43.900 --> 00:14:44.740
– Captain!
– Captain!

230
00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:46.070
Marine Headquarters...!

231
00:14:46.070 --> 00:14:50.040
Where's Robin?! Hand her over, dammit!

232
00:14:50.040 --> 00:14:51.700
That damn jinx!

233
00:14:54.670 --> 00:14:57.170
Your sin is being alive!

234
00:14:58.170 --> 00:15:00.840
What?! Nico Robin is in town?!

235
00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:04.800
Find her! Hand her over to the government!

236
00:15:08.010 --> 00:15:09.600
I found one!

237
00:15:09.600 --> 00:15:11.220
A poneglyph!

238
00:15:11.220 --> 00:15:15.230
Stay away from my shop!
I've got nothing to sell you!

239
00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:17.980
I'm sixteen. I'll do anything.

240
00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:20.230
Please let me join your organization.

241
00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:23.190
You betrayed me, Robin!

242
00:15:23.860 --> 00:15:25.400
Nico Robin.

243
00:15:25.400 --> 00:15:27.530
I'm in need of your assistance.

244
00:15:29.740 --> 00:15:33.500
I heard that you can read poneglyphs.

245
00:15:36.120 --> 00:15:41.250
If... you exercise a buster call
right here, right now...

246
00:15:41.750 --> 00:15:43.920
then not only Enies Lobby...

247
00:15:47.800 --> 00:15:50.680
but every single one of you will be obliterated!

248
00:15:50.680 --> 00:15:52.890
Th-That's the stupidest...!

249
00:15:53.310 --> 00:15:55.890
Our allies know better than to target us!

250
00:15:55.890 --> 00:15:57.480
Just what are you trying to say?!

251
00:15:58.480 --> 00:16:01.730
Twenty years ago,
they took everything from me...

252
00:16:02.650 --> 00:16:05.440
and devastated so many lives...

253
00:16:06.070 --> 00:16:08.200
with just one attack—

254
00:16:08.200 --> 00:16:09.570
a buster call.

255
00:16:10.320 --> 00:16:11.870
And now that attack...

256
00:16:12.280 --> 00:16:16.290
is being directed at the friends
who finally allowed me to lower my guard.

257
00:16:16.290 --> 00:16:23.130
The more I wish to be with you,
the more my fate will threaten you!

258
00:16:23.750 --> 00:16:29.430
No matter how far I travel at sea,
I face a colossal enemy that I can't outrun...

259
00:16:29.970 --> 00:16:34.390
because my enemy is the world itself,
as well as all the darkness therein.

260
00:16:34.390 --> 00:16:37.600
There was the run-in
with Aokiji, and now this...

261
00:16:38.270 --> 00:16:40.350
My troubles have hurt you twice!

262
00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:45.320
If this continues forever,
no matter your best intentions,

263
00:16:47.650 --> 00:16:49.660
you'll eventually see me as a burden!

264
00:16:49.660 --> 00:16:52.910
Then one day, you'll inevitably
betray and abandon me!

265
00:16:52.910 --> 00:16:54.990
That's what I'm most afraid of!

266
00:16:54.990 --> 00:16:58.330
That's why I didn't want you
to come to rescue me!

267
00:16:58.330 --> 00:17:00.000
If I'm as good as dead,

268
00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:03.500
then I choose to die right here, right now!

269
00:17:07.510 --> 00:17:08.630
Robin...

270
00:17:08.630 --> 00:17:10.470
Robin.

271
00:17:11.430 --> 00:17:12.800
Robin...

272
00:17:13.760 --> 00:17:15.760
It all makes sense now.

273
00:17:18.850 --> 00:17:21.850
I see! That is indeed a sound argument!

274
00:17:21.850 --> 00:17:27.570
I mean, no one is stupid enough
to think it's better with you around.

275
00:17:29.570 --> 00:17:31.950
Look at that symbol, you damn pirates!

276
00:17:34.910 --> 00:17:42.790
Its mark symbolizes the unity of over 170 countries,
spanning the four blues and the Grand Line.

277
00:17:42.790 --> 00:17:44.750
This is the world!

278
00:17:45.210 --> 00:17:49.720
Does that hammer home how utterly
insignificant you are against all that?!

279
00:17:50.880 --> 00:17:56.180
Do you understand the sheer size
of the organization chasing this woman?!

280
00:17:56.890 --> 00:17:59.600
I know who Robin's enemy is now.

281
00:18:00.140 --> 00:18:01.350
Sogeking.

282
00:18:03.190 --> 00:18:05.360
Shoot down that flag.

283
00:18:05.730 --> 00:18:06.940
Roger.

284
00:18:08.230 --> 00:18:11.700
This is my new weapon,
a huge slingshot I call Kabuto!

285
00:18:12.070 --> 00:18:14.660
Marvel at its power!

286
00:18:14.660 --> 00:18:18.080
Lethal Firebird Star!

287
00:18:26.960 --> 00:18:27.750
No way!

288
00:18:31.340 --> 00:18:32.550
Mission accomplished.

289
00:18:36.390 --> 00:18:38.100
N-Now they've done it!

290
00:18:38.100 --> 00:18:42.100
Do they understand
what it means to attack a flag?!

291
00:18:42.810 --> 00:18:48.070
Those pirates just declared war
on the World Government!

292
00:18:48.440 --> 00:18:50.320
Are you all insane?!

293
00:18:50.320 --> 00:18:53.780
You're all as good as dead after
making the world your enemy!

294
00:18:53.780 --> 00:18:58.660
Bring it on!

295
00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:09.960
Robin!

296
00:19:11.630 --> 00:19:14.420
We still haven't heard you say it!

297
00:19:19.050 --> 00:19:22.470
Say you want to live!

298
00:19:25.850 --> 00:19:26.850
Robin...

299
00:19:31.320 --> 00:19:32.440
Robin!

300
00:19:34.820 --> 00:19:36.070
To live...

301
00:19:36.780 --> 00:19:40.700
You shouldn't be allowed
to live in this world, Robin!

302
00:19:40.700 --> 00:19:44.910
Your existence itself is a huge crime, Robin!

303
00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.920
This is something I dared not wish for.

304
00:19:52.590 --> 00:19:55.840
No one ever let me wish for it.

305
00:19:56.340 --> 00:19:58.510
I want to die!

306
00:19:58.550 --> 00:20:03.100
The sea is vast, so someday...

307
00:20:03.100 --> 00:20:06.940
you'll find friends who'll protect you!

308
00:20:13.900 --> 00:20:16.400
Believe in Luffy.

309
00:20:18.570 --> 00:20:19.410
If...

310
00:20:20.030 --> 00:20:23.370
it's really okay for me
to utter my wish just once...

311
00:20:24.950 --> 00:20:26.370
I...

312
00:20:28.830 --> 00:20:31.460
I want to live!

313
00:20:31.460 --> 00:20:36.720
Take me back to sea with you!

314
00:20:59.860 --> 00:21:03.910
You guys...! I love you guys, dammit!

315
00:21:05.830 --> 00:21:06.660
Let's go!

316
00:21:12.050 --> 00:21:18.590
I know there’s something that I need to say,

317
00:21:18.970 --> 00:21:22.560
but I can’t seem to find the words

318
00:21:22.810 --> 00:21:30.440
Wandering aimlessly, forever on the hunt, that’s how I’ve lived

319
00:21:30.440 --> 00:21:36.200
And now there’s something right in front of me,

320
00:21:37.400 --> 00:21:40.910
a light that shines brighter than gold

321
00:21:41.280 --> 00:21:46.290
But as I trail behind, it speeds out of sight.

322
00:21:46.290 --> 00:21:52.880
What’s going on? Scared of what’s yet to come

323
00:21:53.210 --> 00:21:59.130
So many times, so many times as we both stumbled on the way

324
00:21:59.340 --> 00:22:02.140
We’ve had our highs, we’ve had our lows;

325
00:22:02.430 --> 00:22:05.220
Yeah, we just take it day by day

326
00:22:05.520 --> 00:22:11.770
Never forget that even when the night snuffs out the light

327
00:22:12.060 --> 00:22:18.400
When the dark has passed the sun will rise again
